<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-04-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-04-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="326" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d326">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Adams</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Seward</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 669.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,
                                        <hi rend="italic">London</hi>,</placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-04-22"><hi rend="italic">April</hi> 22, 1864.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received from Mr. Burlingame, at
                            Pekin, by way of Irkutsk, a telegram dated the 24th of March, to the
                            following effect:</p>
                        <p>“Inform them at Washington that the Chinese government, on my demand, has
                            issued a proclamation forbidding the use of the waters and harbors of
                            China to the confederate cruisers, as well as to furnish them any
                            supplies.”</p>
                        <p>I have the honor to be, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>CHARLES FRANCIS ADAMS</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>